January 14, 2002 08:10 CDT<br>
<br>
Astronomers say they have discovered what may be the precursors of Earth-like planets forming at Earth-like distances and temperatures around a Sun-like star 430 light years away. <br>
<br>
&quot;The structure of the belt of material is consistent with current theories about planet formation in our solar system as well as the dynamical interactions of dust with large planetesimals.&quot; according to Michael Meyer of the University of Arizona. &quot;Although there is no direct evidence for planets surrounding HD 113766, the observations suggest the emergence of a planetary system not unlike our own.&quot;<br>
