<br>
The star, HD 113766A, is located 430 light years away in the direction of Centaurus. The star is number 113766 in Henry Draper's 19th-century catalog of spectral classifications for bright stars. The letter 'A' indicates that it is one member of a binary star pair. Both stars are similar to, but somewhat hotter, more massive, and more luminous, than our Sun. <br>
